*****
[4] Diarrhea - India (Punjab)
Date: Wed 1 Sep 2010
Source: Sify.com [edited]
<http://sify.com/news/gastroenteritis-outbreak-hits-ludhiana-news-national-kjbpkfchjjd.html>


There has been a outbreak of gastroenteritis in Ludhiana and around
34 people have been admitted to local hospitals. Most of the cases
have been registered from the Niwasi Bihari Colony, Sherpur Colony
and Gaspura area of the district, where, according to the
authorities, the disease has broken out mainly due to waterlogging.
Many people have died due to the disease.

Ramesh Tiwari, a resident of the Niwasi Bihari Colony, also said that
the waterborne disease broke out due to continuous waterlogging in the area.

"There is always waterlogging here in this area due to jammed sewage
system. This has caused the outbreak of gastroenteritis in the area.
All the clinics and hospitals in area are full of gastroenteritis
patients," said Tiwari.

Local administration has also confirmed the outbreak, and has said
that the numbers of the cases are increasing every day. "Almost 5 to
6 cases are coming every day. Most of them are coming from a
particular area. Symptoms of the disease are that one suffers from
vomiting, dysentery, and this can lead to dehydration," said Kuldeep
Singh, Assistant Commissioner, Ludhiana.

Within 5 days, gastroenteritis has already taken 19 lives.

[Byline: Karan Kapoor]

